<div class="marketing-static-pages-why">
  <header>
    <h2>Most Harassment Goes Unreported</h3>
  </header>

  <article>
    We need your help to shine a light on harassment in the workplace.
  </article>

  <div class="stats">
    <article>
      <div>
        <header>
          <small>less than</small>
          <h3>5%</h3>
          of incidents are officially reported.
        </header>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article>
      <div>
        <header>
          <small>less than</small>
          <h3>35%</h3>
        </header>
        tell a manager or supervisor.
      </div>
    </article>

    <article>
      <div>
        <header>
          <small>up to</small>
          <h3>2/3rds</h3>
        </header>
        experience retaliation.
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>



  <div class="workings">
    <header>
      <h3>How it Works</h3>
      We make reporting safe and easy.
    </header>

    <section>
      <aside>
        <%= image_tag("marketing/static_pages/why/clipboard.jpg") %>
      </aside>

      <article>
        <div>1</div>
        <div>
          <header>You report your experiences with harassment</header>
          Report your positive and negative experiences with harassment. It
          doesn't matter how serious or minor it is. Just letting us know about
          it goes a long way to bringing more exposure to harassment and
          bullying.
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section>
      <aside>
        <%= image_tag("marketing/static_pages/why/calculate.jpg") %>
      </aside>

      <article>
        <div>2</div>
        <div>
          <header>We crunch the numbers</header>
          We categorize and review reports. Every report gets its own score
          based on over a dozen criteria and metrics.
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section>
      <aside>
        <%= image_tag("marketing/static_pages/why/traffic_light.jpg") %>
      </aside>

      <article>
        <div>3</div>
        <div>
          <header>Everyone can see their rating</header>
          We total up all the incidents and compare it with other companies
          based on type and size of company. We then give every
          company a Coworkability Score.
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>

  <article>
    <br />
    Help by telling us your experiences. Good or bad, big or small, we want to
    hear.
    <small>
      Maybe you were teased, or embarrassed in front of others. Maybe you had
      pranks pulled on you. Or maybe you work at a great company and want to
      give them credit. We want to hear everyone's story. Get started by
      searching below.
    </small>
  </article>
</div>
